ng for something...anything that would put them on par with the Zerker.  Adding Fluff will only hold so many.  Flurry is nice and all...but as stated before...what good is an ability that can only be used on one person per fight since RvR combat usually last less then a minute.  We as Mercs dont want more buttons to push.  And Im sure BM think the same way.  I look at the damage output that a Zerker has and compare it to almost anyother class and it pathetic.  I have seen screen shots of some Zerkers doing well over 400 damage per hit.  My Necro that I have does that type of damage only because of spells and the mobs I select.  My Merc.  LOL.  I only wish I could see that type of damage.  Even if I had my Dex dropped to nothing and Str capped I still would never see that it seems.  I have almost given up on the Merc class altogether since we lack in offense and defense.  We spec in DW to get a better chance to hit with out second weapon...thats fine and dandy.  But it has no bonus to hit...No bonus to damage..and the styles we have that either slow or what not it breaks.  Defense is only good in PvE since as I stated above parry and shield still are bugged in RvR.  I can parry mobs like crazy.  But once I go up against an enemy player Id be lucky to parry once it seems.  To me and just about everyone else that I have talked to think that DW/CD/LA should all work the same.  I can understand that in real life different places to things differently.  But for common game play and game dynamics they would make them the same for balancing issues.<br>
